erns directly with them.&#10;3. A finance committee motion is mentioned, which was unanimously passed, calling for funding the Auditor General in full. However, the transcript does not provide information on whether the government has explicitly responded to or addressed this motion.&#10;4. The Prime Minister, Right Hon. Justin Trudeau, focuses on introducing a bill to help Canadians with the Canada emergency response benefit and those living with disabilities while proposing a debate and vote on the matter to the opposition parties. He does not directly address the Auditor General's funding situation in his statement.&#10;&#10;In summary, the government has not explicitly stated that they are withholding funds from the Auditor General's office based on the provided transcript. While the opposition party has raised concerns about insufficient resources for conducting audits and has passed a unanimous motion at the finance committee to fund the Auditor General in full, there is no clear indication of the government's position or response regarding this matter.">
