usinesses, including sole proprietors, during the pandemic.&#10;3. The opposition parties and the Parliamentary Budget Officer have called for an economic update, but the government has not committed to this. They argue that their daily updates provide sufficient transparency regarding their measures and investments in response to the pandemic.&#10;4. While there is no direct connection between gun buybacks and support for sole proprietors in the provided materials, it's important to note that small business owners can expect additional support to qualify for COVID-19 relief funding within about a week, according to the Minister of Small Business, Export Promotion and International Trade.&#10;5. In conclusion, instead of spending funds on gun buybacks, those resources could be directed towards supporting sole proprietors who cannot access COVID-19 relief funding due to not having a business chequing account. However, this comparison is based on the assumption that the government plans to allocate a certain amount of money for firearms buybacks, which has not been explicitly stated. Small businesses can expect additional support for COVID-19 relief within about a week.">
