re urging the Government of Canada to implement a guaranteed, consistent, national, and livable universal basic income system for all Canadians because it would provide a safety net during crises like the global pandemic, help lift people out of poverty, enable affordability of essential needs such as safe housing and transportation, and foster an overdue conversation on this matter. This call is related to the recommendations from the National Inquiry into Missing and Murdered Indigenous Women and Girls, which also suggested establishing a guaranteed annual livable income for all Canadians. A universal basic income system could help address systemic issues contributing to ongoing violence against indigenous women and girls in Canada.">
